me":"Spirit","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/e47c2d/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-05-14T21:02:03.108Z","cooked":"<p>We are using 2 Phoenix motors with (I believe) 4 to 1 gear boxes on them, the ctr electronics wcp thoroughbore encoder for 1/2 (I believe it’s the newest cancoder of this type).</p>
<p>The encoder sits on the lowest shaft of the elevator, and really we are just trying to get it to do anything at this point <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/pensive.png?v=12" title=":pensive:" class="emoji" alt=":pensive:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"></p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2025-05-14T21:02:03.108Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":89,"readers_count":88,"score":27.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":501731,"topic_slug":"c-double-elevator-help-seeking-reference-code","display_username":"Eren","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":13396,"username":"Dkt01","name":"Dkt01","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/dkt01/{size}/4603_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":75780,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/c-double-elevator-help-seeking-reference-code/501731/6","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3624703,"name":"Dkt01","username":"Dkt01","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/dkt01/{size}/4603_2.png","created_at":"2025-05-14T21:02:15.548Z","cooked":"<p>Looks like you have two motors controlling the same moving component.  You should have one motor act as a follower (<a href="https://v6.docs.ctr-electronics.com/en/stable/docs/migration/migration-guide/control-requests-guide.html#follower-motors" rel="noopener nofollow ugc"><span class="abbreviation">CTRE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Cross The Road Electronics"></template></span> example</a>).  Make sure the follower motor is properly inverted if it needs to spin in the opposite direction as the leader</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2025-05-14T21:02:15.548Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":89,"readers_count":88,"score":22.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":501731,"topic_slug":"c-double-elevator-help-seeking-reference-code","display_username":"Dkt01","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://v6.docs.ctr-electronics.com/en/stable/docs/migration/migration-guide/control-requests-guide.html#follower-motors","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Control Requests","clicks":3}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":75780,"username":"Spirit","name":"Eren","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/e47c2d/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":13396,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"1756 Argos: Programming Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/c-double-elevator-help-seeking-reference-code/501731/7","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3624746,"name":"Aidan","username":"FieryFuryGame","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/fieryfurygame/{size}/262141_2.png","created_at":"2025-05-14T21:54:52.219Z","cooked":"<p>I was able to find the GitHub page for your code (as far as I can tell):</p><aside class="onebox githubblob" data-onebox-src="https://github.com/LovelandHighRobotics1977/1977-Reefscape/blob/Test.Bot/src/main/cpp/Subsystems/Drivetrain/Mechanism/Coral.cpp">
